  "prompt": "Who are some of the best lawyers in India?",
  "response": "Identifying the \"best\" lawyers can be subjective as it often depends on the area of law and individual needs. However, several prominent lawyers in India are frequently recognized for their expertise, impact on high-profile cases, and contributions to the legal field. Some of these include:\n\n1. **Fali S. Nariman** - A constitutional law expert, Nariman is a highly respected senior advocate and has been involved in numerous landmark cases.\n\n2. **Harish Salve** - Known for his expertise in constitutional and commercial law, Salve has represented India at international forums as well.\n\n3. **Arvind Datar** - A senior advocate known for his work on constitutional and tax matters.\n\n4. **Gopal Subramanium** - A former Solicitor General of India, Subramanium has a reputation for handling complex legal issues.\n\n5. **Mukul Rohatgi** - A former Attorney General of India, Rohatgi is notable for his role in high-profile cases.\n\n6. **Indira Jaising** - A prominent lawyer known for her work in human rights and women's rights, Jaising has been a pioneering figure in public interest litigation.\n\n7. **Kapil Sibal** - A senior advocate and politician, Sibal has been involved in various significant legal battles.\n\n8. **Abhishek Manu Singhvi** - Known for his work in constitutional, commercial, and insolvency laws.\n\n9. **K.K. Venugopal** - Serving as the Attorney General of India, Venugopal is an accomplished expert in constitutional law.\n\n10. **Soli Sorabjee** - Though he passed away in 2021, Sorabjee was a notable senior advocate and former Attorney General known for his work in human rights.\n\nThe legal landscape in India is continually evolving, and many lawyers are making significant contributions across various fields of law. It's important for individuals to research and find a lawyer with the experience and expertise suited to their specific legal needs.",
